caption.body: "Wherever in the world you want to go...the world's largest fleet of over-ocean Jets is at your service...the Pan Am Jet Clipper Fleet"  Pioneering jet travel with the Boeing 707, and later the 747, Pan American World Airways emphasized its position as the "World's Most Experienced Airline". Advertising their fleet of jets including the Douglas DC-8C and Boeing 707's, Pan Am claimed that "nearly half of all the over-ocean jetliners in service are Pan Am Jet Clippers." Have you ever flown on a Pan Am Jet?  Image: Pan American World Airways advertisement, Saturday Evening Post, 1960s. Gift of Barnaby Conrad III. 2001.038.164.002.
